  "prompt": "DiD the members of indian constituent assembly help J&k in making of their constitution?",
  "response": "The members of the Indian Constituent Assembly did play a role in the formation of Jammu and Kashmir's constitution, but it was not a direct drafting process. Here are the key points:\n\n1. After India's independence, J&K was a princely state with a special status under the instrument of accession.\n\n2. Sheikh Abdullah, as the leader of the National Conference, was instrumental in drafting the J&K constitution.\n\n3. The Constituent Assembly of J&K was formed in 1951, which was different from the Indian Constituent Assembly.\n\n4. While the Indian Constituent Assembly provided guidance and constitutional framework, the J&K constitution was primarily drafted by local leaders.\n\n5. The J&K constitution was adopted on 17 November 1956, which was distinct from the Indian Constitution adopted in 1950.\n\n6. The J&K constitution reflected the state's unique autonomy and special provisions under Article 370.\n\nSo while the Indian Constituent Assembly didn't directly draft the J&K constitution, they did provide a broader constitutional context and framework within which J&K developed its own constitution.",
